## Core Requirements

**Primary Goal**: Extract accurate bounding box coordinates for every visual element (figures, images, tables, charts, diagrams) in the document. These coordinates will be used for automated image extraction, so precision is critical.

## Bounding Box Format

For EVERY visual element, include bounding box coordinates as a data attribute:
- Format: `data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2"`
- Coordinate system: 0-1000 scale where:
  - (0,0) = top-left corner of the page
  - (1000,1000) = bottom-right corner of the page
- Example: `<figure data-bbox="125,200,875,600">` represents a figure that:
  - Starts at 12.5% from left, 20% from top
  - Ends at 87.5% from left, 60% from top

## HTML Structure Requirements

### Visual Elements
```html
<figure data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2" class="page-N-figure" id="figure-N">
  <figcaption>Figure N: Caption text</figcaption>
</figure>

<table data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2" class="page-N-table" id="table-N">
  <caption>Table N: Caption text</caption>
  <!-- table content -->
</table>

<img data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2" class="page-N-image" alt="Description" />

<div data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2" class="page-N-diagram">
  <!-- diagram content -->
</div>
```

